04259nam a22006375i 9780823295531DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20211999nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232955317 a10.1515/97808232955312doi  a(DE-B1597)575255  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aLIT0040202bisacsh1 aGiannone, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFlannery O'Connor and the Mystery of Love /cRichard Giannone. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2021] 4cÂ©1999  a1 online resource (268 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tNote on Texts -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Price of Guilt -- t2 Looking for a Good Man -- t3 Finding the Good Man -- t4 The Price of Love -- t5 Convergence -- t6 Preparation -- t7 Fulfillment -- t8 First and Last Things -- tAppendix -- tBibliography -- tIndex to O'Connor's Works -- tGeneral Index -- tA Note on the Author0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFlannery O'Connor and the Mystery of Love interprets O'Connor's perplexing fiction on its own terms. By stepping back from prevailing controversies, this seminal study takes the pleasure of turning to the short stories and novels themselves and forming an impression of them while seeking the answers to such questions as they necessarily suggest themselves. This goal inevitably entails a consideration of the hardness and violence that are the hallmark of O'Connor's genius. That severity for Giannone is inseparable from O'Connor's recounting, in her words, "the action of grace." God's bounty can leave its beneficiaries with some very real handicaps. Grace in this fiction can make the blood run cold; it can do real injury to the body; and it can annihilate. These devastations paradoxically prepare the characters to receive and give compassion. In its numerous and disturbing forms, the coupling of violence and hardship with divine favor marks the mature nature of O'Connor's Christianity. Suffering is found at heart of love and is its hidden face, agonized and abandoned. This is a love that is an anomaly and an enigma, for the wracked human body holds the glimmer of good omen. Flannery O'Connor and the Mystery of Love traces the evolution of these gaping wounds of love to show how they present the same challenge to her readers as to her characters, all of whom must learn that we are worth what our love is worth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311118960408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z97831107432960 cprintz978082321911740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329553140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823295531423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823295531/original  a978-3-11-074329-6  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-118960-4  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK